<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
VRChat comes with a whole host of social tools for users. Such as friends, invites, notes, and more!
</div>

<span id="User_profiles"></span>
<div class="mw-translate-fuzzy">
== Profile użytkowników ==
</div>
[[File:UserProfile.webp|thumb|<span lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">VRChat's User Profile.</span>]]
<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
Introduced in the [https://docs.vrchat.com/docs/vrchat-202123 Identity Update], user profiles are a personalized space where information is displayed about a user. Information on a user's profile includes [[Special:MyLanguage/Social#Statuses|status]], [[Special:MyLanguage/Trust_Rank|trust rank]], [[Special:MyLanguage/Social#Pronouns|pronouns]], bio, current [[Special:MyLanguage/Instances|instance]] (if applicable), languages they speak, social links, [[Special:MyLanguage/Badges|badges]] they own, and the [[Special:MyLanguage/Groups|groups]] they're in.
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
Under a user's profile, there are several [[Special:MyLanguage/Social#Actions|actions]] you can take - such as sending a friend request or an invite to an instance.
</div>

<span id="Statuses"></span>
=== Statusy ===

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
Statuses can be set in the [[Special:MyLanguage/Quick Menu|Quick Menu]], [[Special:MyLanguage/Main Menu|Main Menu]], or on the {{VRC link|https://vrchat.com/home|VRChat Website}} and are used for the following: to control how easily a user's friends can join their instance, to vary whether a user's friends can see the instance they are currently in, to silence notifications, and to communicate an activity.
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
Statuses consist of a color and a customizable short sentence (up to 32 characters). There are four different statuses in VRChat:
</div>

{| class="wikitable"
! scope="col" style="width:13em" |Status
!Opis
|-
|<div style="background-color:rgb(66, 202, 255);width:1rem;height:1rem;border-radius:9999px;display:inline-block;margin:0 0.5em -0.1em 0.5em" alt="Blue"></div>Dołącz do mnie (Niebieski)
|<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
Your friends can see the instance you are in and may join freely with identical rules to [[Special:MyLanguage/Social#Statuses|Online]] status.
However, if the [[Special:MyLanguage/Instances|instance]] is private and unviewable, all invite requests from friends are automatically accepted as long as you have permission to accept them.
</div>
|-
|<div style="background-color:rgb(81, 229, 126);width:1rem;height:1rem;border-radius:9999px;display:inline-block;margin:0 0.5em -0.1em 0.5em" alt="Green"></div>Online (Zielony)
|<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
Your friends can see the instance you are in and can join your instance without an invitation.
However, your friends may not see or join the instance without an invite if the instance is deemed "private".
Your instance is viewable and joinable by friends without requesting an invite in the following cases:
*The instance is [[Special:MyLanguage/Worlds#Instance Types|Friends+]], [[Special:MyLanguage/Worlds#Instance Types|Group+]], [[Special:MyLanguage/Worlds#Instance Types|Public]], or [[Special:MyLanguage/Worlds#Instance Types|Group Public]].
*The instance is [[Special:MyLanguage/Worlds#Instance Types|Friends]] and either you or a mutual friend are the instance creator.
*The instance is [[Special:MyLanguage/Worlds#Instance Types|Group]] and your friends are a member of the group with permission to join the instance based on their group roles.
*The instance is [[Special:MyLanguage/Worlds#Instance Types|Invite]] or [[Special:MyLanguage/Worlds#Instance Types|Invite+]] and your friends are returning to the instance they created.
</div>
|-
|<div style="background-color:rgb(232, 129, 52);width:1rem;height:1rem;border-radius:9999px;display:inline-block;margin:0 0.5em -0.1em 0.5em" alt="Orange"></div>Zapytaj mnie (Pomarańczowy)
|<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
Your friends cannot see the instance you are in.
They must request an invite from you to be able to join, regardless of the instance's privacy.
</div>
|-
|<div style="background-color:rgb(91, 11, 11);width:1rem;height:1rem;border-radius:9999px;display:inline-block;margin:0 0.5em -0.1em 0.5em" alt="Red"></div>Nie przeszkadzać (Czerwony)
|<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
Your friends cannot see the instance you are in. They may request to join, but you will not receive any notifications. In fact, you won't be able to send or request any invites to your friends within the game if they are in that status.
* Incoming friend requests are delivered quietly to the "Friend Requests" Inbox.
* A response for a request (ex. invite request) you send out, will be displayed.
* Group notifications are disabled.
</div>
|}
<span id="Pronouns"></span>
=== Zaimki ===

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
[[wikipedia:Pronoun|Pronouns]] can be displayed on one's bio to indicate to others how to refer to them. When set, pronouns will be displayed on your bio, and also displayed under your [[Special:MyLanguage/Nameplates|nameplate]].
<gallery>
Pronouns1.webp|Displayed in the bio on the website
Pronouns3.webp|Displayed in the bio in game
Pronouns2.webp|Displayed in the bio on mobile client
</gallery>
</div>

===Bio===

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
The bio (abbreviation for biography) is a paragraph of text written by the user that is generally used to describe or introduce themselves but can be used for any purpose. The bio can be up to 500 characters long.
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
Currently, emoji and some special symbols(e.g. fractions) are not supported. Some known special characters that are allowed are:
